<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4906779>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 5. Morphological characters of Hemicrepidius. Tarsi, lateral view: a) H. memnonius, b) H. bilobatus, scale bar between = 1 mm. Antenna types: c) Strongly serrate, with triangular antennomere 3 (H. niger), d) Serrate, with impunctate medial line (ml, arrow) of antennomeres (H. memnonius), e) Serrate, lacking medial line (H. californicus), f) Weakly serrate (H. hemipodus), all to scale, scale bar below d = 1 mm. Mesothorax: g) Lateral edges of mesothorax raised in near 90-degree angle, arrow (H. californicus), stepped line to highlight character, scale bar below body = 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4906779/files/figure.png" .

